Version 2.0.5
--------------
2012-02-13 erra <erra@ya.ru>
	* ircd/s_misc.c,rusnet/rusnet_cmds.c: code clearance (unused variables)

2012-02-12 erra <erra@ya.ru>
	* ircd/res.c: hostbuf and hostbuf2 made 1 byte bigger
	* ircd/s_auth.c,ircd/s_bsd.c: buffer in sendto_iauth increased to pass
			MAXHOSTLEN domain names

Version 2.0.4
--------------
2012-02-11 erra <erra@ya.ru>
	* ircd/res.c: memory allocation inside and after IDN decoding
			fixed (found by denk)
	* ircd/s_misc.c: DNS names limit fixed

2012-02-09 erra <erra@ya.ru>
	* iauth/a_struct_def.h: MAXHOSTLEN used for hostnames
	* ircd/res.c: MAXHOSTLEN used for hostnames and buffers

Version 2.0.3
--------------
2012-01-30 erra <erra@ya.ru>
	* common/support.c: heap corruption prevented in cstrip (found by denk)

2012-01-29 erra <erra@ya.ru>
	* common/support.c: ISUPPORT reply extended with FNC and CASEMAPPING
	* ircd/s_conf.c: buffer overflow prevented in attach_Iline (by denk)

Version 2.0.2
--------------
2011-11-13 erra <erra@ya.ru>
	* common/struct_def.h: MAXHOSTLEN defined
	* ircd/s_conf.c: increase DNS names buffer to MAXHOSTLEN;
			do not try DEFAULT_CHARSET for OLD8BIT
	* ircd/s_misc.c: handle oversized DNS names
	* rusnet/rusnet_codepages.c, rusnet/rusnet_init.c: code clearance
	* support/configure.in, support/configure: typo fixed in zlib detection

2011-10-21 erra <erra@ya.ru>
	* ircd/s_err.c: RPL_IDENTIFIED and RPL_NOCOLOR fixed

Version 2.0.1
--------------
2011-10-14 erra <erra@ya.ru>
	* ircd/channel.c: match_modeid fixed

2011-10-14 erra <erra@ya.ru>
	* common/send.c: send_message(): stop if fd < 0
	* support/configure, support/configure.in: sun cc test added

2011-10-13 denk <denis@tambov.ru>
	* ircd/s_bsd.c: setsockopt for IPV6_V6ONLY moved to inetport() and
			applied for listening ports only

Version 2.0
--------------
2011-10-10 erra <erra@ya.ru>
	* ircd/channel.c: channel name buffer increased to avoid join !longname
			coredumps caused by sprintf() buffer overrun

2011-10-03 erra <erra@ya.ru>
	* ircd/channel.c: topic setting by ChanServ fixed

2011-10-01 erra <erra@ya.ru>
	* ircd/s_bsd.c: setsockopt for IPV6_V6ONLY considered okay if
			error code is ENOPROTOOPT

2011-09-30 erra <erra@ya.ru>
	* common/send.c: definition for _NO_IP_ fixed
	* ircd/s_conf.c: code clearance

2011-09-30 denk <denis@tambov.ru>
	* ircd/res.c: IPv6 support fixed
	* ircd/s_bsd.c: IPv6 support fixed (disable IPv6-only sockets)

2011-09-29 denk <denis@tambov.ru>
	* ircd/res.c, ircd/res_init.c, ircd/resolv_def.h: IPv6 support added

2011-09-28 erra <erra@ya.ru>
	* common/match.c, common/sm_loop.c: patterns narrowed to * and ? only
			if no extended pattern flag (FNM_RNGMATCH) set

2011-09-26 erra <erra@ya.ru>
	* ircd/channel.c: check_spam call condition by bird_of_luck

2011-09-22 erra <erra@ya.ru>
	* common/support.c: cstrip() cycle refined
	* ircd/s_misc.c: check_triggers() call removed from exit_one_client
	* ircd/s_serv.c: /stats K/R/E fixed (CONF_TRIGGER was messed with
			CONF_TLINE)
	* ircd/s_user.c: check_triggers() call added to m_quit; guardian check
			for NULL message added to check_spam
	* ircd/s_user_ext.h: removed EXTERN declaration for check_triggers()

2011-09-20 erra <erra@ya.ru>
	* common/support.c, common/support_ext.h: cstrip() added for
			stripping colors from spam messages before checking
	* ircd/channel.c: check_spam call added to m_part()
	* ircd/s_conf.c: do not decode ircd.conf/kills.conf unless
			DECODE_CONFIG was defined at compile time
	* ircd/s_debug.c: STRIP_COLORS is shown as 'b' in server_opts
	* ircd/s_err.c: RPL_STATSTRIGGER fixed
	* ircd/s_serv.c: /stats T output fixed
	* ircd/s_user.c: check_spam() created to be called from m_message
			as well as m_part and exit_one_client
	* support/config.h.dist: STRIP_COLORS added, defined by default;
			DECODE_CONFIG added, undef by default

2011-09-20 erra <erra@ya.ru>
	* ircd/s_serv.c: m_trigger/m_untrigger fixed for optional class

2011-09-18 erra <erra@ya.ru>
	* common/match.c: bzero used instead of {0} assignment for mbs
	* ircd/s_user.c: condition fixed in check_triggers
	* ircd/s_serv.c: condition fixed in match_trigger

2011-09-15 erra <erra@ya.ru>
	* ircd/s_serv.c: m_trigger/m_untrigger for T:lines, /stats T
	* iserv/iserv.c: T:lines processing introduced

2011-09-14 erra <erra@ya.ru>
	* */*: #ifdef RUSNET_RLINES removed (now mandatory)
	* common/numeric_def.h, common/struct_def.h, ircd/s_err.c,
		ircd/s_user.c: usermode +c (colorless) added
	* ircd/channel.c: discard mode +R for older servers; restore mode
			assignment (affected modes with args)

2011-09-13 erra <erra@ya.ru>
	* common/send.c: colorless code cancelled (erroneous)
	* ircd/channel.c: discard colorful PART message for colorless channels
	* ircd/s_user.c: whois opnotice fixed

2011-09-12 erra <erra@ya.ru>
	* common/collsyms.h, common/match.c, common/sm_loop.c: GNU bash wchar
			matching code imported
	* support/Makefile.in: match.o dependencies updated

2011-09-11 erra <erra@ya.ru>
	* common/conversion.c: ICONV_CHAR definition adjusted for FreeBSD
	* common/os.h: #include <wctype.h> for FreeBSD
	* ircd/ircd.c: ttyname usage refined (code clearance)
	* ircd/res_init.c: redefinition of _D_UNUSED_ cancelled (code clearance)
	* ircd/s_auth.c: typo fixed in debugging code (code clearance)
	* ircd/s_conf.c: unused type conversion cancelled (code clearance)
	* ircd/s_id.c: signed/unsigned conversion (code clearance)
	* ircd/s_serv.c: check_tconfs marked out (not really used)
	* support/configure, support/configure.in: -I/usr/local/include for
			idna.h under FreeBSD

