	* common/send.c: sendto_log moved ahead to avoid compilation
			error on gcc; when open fd found for a log,
			it gets reused, no multiple descriptors for
			a same log anymore

1.4.3_014 ()
2005-09-17 skold <chourf@deware.com>
	* common/send.c: buffer overflow fix in sendto_log (from slcio)
	* ircd/s_conf.c: do_restrict() fix for restricted ('%') username.
	* rusnet/rusnet_cmds.c: umode +h stripped from code
		
2005-09-17 skold <chourf@deware.com>
	* ircd/s_serv.c, channel.c, send.c, common/struct_def.h, parse.c, 
		support/config.h.dist: wallops now optionally send the stuff to
			&WALLOPS channel if WALLOPS_TO_CHANNEL is defined.
			Now available for opers.
			
2005-09-17 slcio <silence@irc.run.net>
	* common/parse.c, struct_def.h: #define LOCOP_TLINE/OPER_TLINE for
			opers/locops temporary lines management.


1.4.3_013 (R1_4_3_013)
2005-09-12 erra <erra@rinet.ru>
	* ircd/s_conf.c, ircd/s_conf_ext.h: disregard bounce and continue
			searching an appropriate I:line when the server
			stated in relevant B:line is not in a network.

2005-09-12 skold <>
	* ircd/list.c: changes to make_server(), make_client(), free_server(),
			free_client()

2005-09-07 skold <chourf@deware.com>
	* ircd/list.c/free_server(),make_server(): additional free()-loops
			detection added
	* ircd/ircd.c, support/config.h.dist: DISABLE_DOUBLE_CONNECTS option
			adopted from 2.11 to overcome problems with two
			autoconnects to each other, try_connections()
			re-designed (adopted from 2.11)

1.4.3_012 (R1_4_3_012)
2005-09-04 skold <chourf@deware.com>
	* ircd/s_user.c: host encryption coredump fix. Hosts with numeric tlds
			should not be sent to the uplink servers causing uplink
			segfault. Issue a KILL instead.

2005-09-03 slcio <silence@irc.run.net>
	* support/Makefile.in: codepagedir fix

2005-09-01 skold <chourf@deware.com>
	* common/send.c, common/send_ext.h, ircd/list.c, s_misc.c, s_user.c,
		s_user_ext.h, support/config.h.dist, common/struct_def.h:
			buffer overflow in sendto_log() fixed, sendto_flog()
			re-designed, latest logging patch (fd merge) rejected.
			Upgrade to this version is required if you are running
			p11 or p10.

1.4.3_011 ()

2005-08-28 slcio <silence@irc.run.net>
	* common/send.c: incorrect vhost sending in vsendpreprep()

2005-08-27 slcio <silence@irc.run.net>
	* many files: get rid of __P()

2005-08-26 skold <chourf@deware.com>
	* support/configure.in, configure: -lcrypto fix when no library found,
			non-blocking detection fix
	* common/support.c, support_ext.h: MyFree(char *) changed to MyFree(void *),
			gcc-4.x will not compile {(char *)(x) = NULL}.

2005-08-24 erra <erra@rinet.ru>
	* common/struct_def.h, ircd/channel.c, ircd/channel_ext.h,
		ircd/s_user.c: new chanmode introduced: "Half-Op" (+h, "%")
	* common/struct_def.h, ircd/s_serv.c: SV_2_11 branch for future
			reference: must increment protocol version to 0211
			when FORCE is changed to SVSNICK and thus split
			versions completely

2005-08-23 erra <erra@rinet.ru>
	* iauth/mod_dnsbl.c: using DNS-based whitelists as well as black-lists

2005-08-23 lost <LoSt@lucky.net>
	* common/send.c, struct_def.h: logging improvements, one open fd per file, 
	    not per l:line

1.4.3_010 (R1_4_3_010)

2005-08-23 lost <LoSt@lucky.net>
	* ircd/s_serv.c: fix for server descriptions: too long description was trimmed 
	    when didn't fit in buffer
	
2005-08-21 slcio <silence@irc.run.net>
	* common/support.c, iauth/a_io.c, ircd/s_bsd.c, iserv/i_io.c,
		support/Makefile.in, support/config.h.dist, ssl_cert:
			sparc-solaris-2.[7-9] platforms are now fully supported.
	    
2005-08-20 skold <chourf@deware.com>, slcio <silence@irc.run.net>
	* support/configure.in, Makefile.in, config.guess, config.h.dist,
		config.sub, configure, setup.h.in, common/os.h: configure.in
			completely rewritten, openssl detection re-designed,
			ancient macros deleted
	* irc/*: client support removed
	* a lot of files: get rid of SPRINTF, mystr[n]cmp. strcase[n]cmp points
			to my[n]cmp, USE_STDARG defines
	
2005-08-18 skold <chourf@deware.com>
	* common/struct_def.h, ircd/ircd.c, ircd_ext.h, s_bsd.c, s_bsd_ext.h,
		s_conf.c, s_user.c, ssl.c, ssl.h: multiple SSL cleanups and
			bug-fixes. Bugs in rehash when listener changed from
			non-ssl to ssl and vice versa, REHASH ssl now only 
			re-initializes SSL library and certificates, REHASH P
			now reloads all listeners from configuration. Change
			P->p and p->P on-the-fly without port re-opening.
	
2005-08-17 slcio <silence@irc.run.net>
	* ircd/channel.c: IsRusnetServices() placement corrections.
	* ircd/ssl.c: coredump in disable_ssl() fixed.
	
2005-08-15 lost <LoSt@lucky.net>
	* common/send.c, send_ext.h, struct_def.h, iauth/a_log_def.h,
		ircd/ircd.c, ircd_signal.c, s_bsd.c, s_conf.c, s_misc.c,
		s_serv.c, s_user.c, iserv/i_log_def.h, support/config.h.dist:
			new logging configurable from ircd.conf, not from
			config.h. Read RUSNET_DOC for details.

2005-08-15 skold <chourf@deware.com>
	* ircd/ircd.c, s_bsd.c: fix for daemonize() from 2.11: incorrect
			descriptors closing, caused server instability upon
			restart, ancient BOOT_CONSOLE removed.

2005-08-14 lost <LoSt@lucky.net>
	* common/common_def.h: isvalid() macro stripped some ukrainian
			symbols, fixed

1.4.3_009 (R1_4_3_009)

2005-08-12 skold <chourf@deware.com>
	* ircd/ircd.c: daemonize() moved  before initconf() is called. 
			Some active descriptors, e.g. listening sockets,  may
			allocate numbers like stderr (2) and will be
			occasionally closed by fork.

2005-08-10 slcio <silence@irc.run.net>
	* ircd/s_user.c, common/parse.c, struct_def.h: IsRusnetServices() macro
	* ircd/channel.c, s_user.c: allow remote cmode, kick, topic, invite,
			notice for IsRusnetServices()
	* ircd/channel.c: allow remote NAMES for IsOper()
	* ircd/s_serv.c: show ssl ports in report_listeners()
		
2005-08-01 skold <chourf@deware.com>
	* ircd/s_serv.c: support for timestamps in T-lines, not only hours in
			handle_tline().
			- fix for incorrect servermasks broadcasting in
			sendto_slaves()
			- fix for colons in T-line reasons, replace them with
			commas
			
2005-08-01 skold <chourf@deware.com>
	* common/numeric_def.h, ircd/s_bsd.c, s_err.c, support/config.h.dist: 
			RPL_HELLO for unregistered clients, local replies array 
			extended up to size 20
	* common/struct_def.h, irc/c_numeric.c, ircd/ircd.c, s_err.c, s_serv.c:
			RPL_TRACELOG removed
	* common/parse.c, struct_def.h, s_bsd.c, s_bsd_ext.h, s_misc.c, s_serv.c: 
			m_reconnect(), close_held(), hold_server() calls removed
	* common/send.c, ircd/s_bsd.c, s_misc.c, s_user.c: #ifdef UNIXPORT fixes
	* common/struct_def.h, ircd/ircd.c, s_conf.c, s_misc.c, s_misc_ext.h, 
		s_serv.c, support/config.h.dist: 
			CACHED_MOTD is now by default, read_motd() now behaves 
			correctly on  no '\n' at the end of file
	* common/struct_def.h, ircd/ircd.c, s_bsd.c, s_conf.c: isListening()
			renamed into isListener()
	* common/struct_def.h, ircd/ircd.c, ircd_ext.h, s_bsd.c, s_bsd_ext.h, 
		s_debug.c, s_misc.c, s_serv.c, support/config.h.dist: 
			DELAY_CLOSE feature for delaying connection close for
			fast reconnecting clients backported from 2.11
	* common/struct_def.h, ircd/s_bsd.c: EXITC_* codes backported from 2.11
			for future use
	* common/support.c, support_ext.h, ircd/chkconf.c, s_conf.c,
		iserv/iserv.c: dgets() rewritten (from 2.11)
	* ircd/channel.c: too many channels in PART might get truncated
			resulted in network desync
	* ircd/ircd.c, ircd_ext.h, s_bsd.c: listeners removed from local[] into
			linked list ListenerLL
	* ircd/ircd.c, s_bsd.c: iauth is now working on cygwin, daemonize(), 
			open_debugfile() backported
	* ircd/ircd_signal.c: SIGUSR1 removed from iauth handlers
	* ircd/list.c, ircd.c, s_bsd.c, s_conf.c: serverbooting status variable 
			added to control if we still have TTY to print to
	* ircd/s_bsd.c, s_bsd_ext.h: dolisten flag added to inetport() for
			future use with P:line flags
	* ircd/s_bsd.c, s_bsd_ext.h: open_listener(), reopen_listeners() calls
			added to work with listening sockets
	* ircd/s_bsd.c: iauth sending optimized (backported from 2.11)
	* ircd/s_bsd.c, s_bsd_ext.h: close_client_fd() to close existing client 
			socket, add_connection_refuse() (backported from 2.11)
	* ircd/s_bsd.c: close_connection() nextconnect can be 0, this might
			cause autoconnect stopped completely
	* ircd/s_bsd.c: LISTENER_MAXACCEPT defined instead of hardcoded 10 to 
			determine how many connections will be accepted at
			a time
	* ircd/s_bsd.c, support/config.h.dist: read_message(): LISTENER_DELAY
			for accepting new connections (backported)
	* ircd/s_serv.c: report_listeners() to show configured listening ports
			and statistics on STATS P. STATS p and STATS P are now
			different
	
1.4.3_008 (R1_4_3_008)

2005-06-15 cj <cj@deware.com>
	* ircd/s_conf.c: check_tlines() coredump fixed


2005-05-31 cj <cj@deware.com>
	* iserv/iserv.c: signals setup changed. SIGUSR2 is now ignored,
			SIGHUP makes logfiles/syslog reloading, SIGTERM/SIGINT
			result in module exiting.

2005-05-30 cj <cj@deware.com>
	* ircd/s_user.c, rusnet/rusnet_cmds.c: internal flag for m_nick()
			should fix problem with collision handling for
			usermodes +r/+R.

2005-05-30 witch <witch@amber.ff.phys.spbu.ru>
	* ircd/s_user.c: m_umode() switch/case re-written into if/else for
			reliable updates

2005-05-25 skold <>
	* common/match.c, struct_def.h, common_def.h: new character array
			ported from hybrid code, old array and macros will
			be deprecated in future builds.
	* ircd/s_serv.c: nonwilds() adopted from hybrid code to control
			suicidal opers.

2005-05-15 skold <chourf@deware.com>
	* ircd/s_conf.c, s_conf_ext.h: find_kill(), find_rline() replaced
			with check_tlines()
	* ircd/s_serv.c: handle_tline(), sendto_slaves(), send_tline_one(),
			rehash_tline() added to support dynamic temporary
			lines configuration.

2005-05-15 silencio <silence@irc.run.net>
	* ircd/s_serv.c: match_tline() for server side temporary lines matching
	* ircd/s_serv.c: STATS r moved to STATS t output. STATS r now is equal
			to STATS R
			
2005-05-13 silencio <silence@irc.run.net>
	* iserv/iserv.c, iserv.h: corrections to the buffered file operations
	* iserv/iserv.c: correction for hostmask reading backward compatibility
	* ircd/s_user.c, s_serv.c: remove strcmp with SERVICES_HOST from code
	* ircd/ircd.c, s_conf.c: USE_SERVICES define removed from rusnet
			services related code.
	* ircd/*: move K-line exempts outside from RUSNET_IRCD define
	* ircd/ircd.c: checkpings() use check_tlines() instead of dummy
			find_kill()
	* ircd/s_conf.c, common/struct_def.h: separate E flag to rehash
			exempts (E-lines) added
	
2005-05-12 skold <chourf@deware.com>
	* iserv/i_log.c, i_log_ext.h, iserv.h: reliable logging implemented
	* iserv/iserv.c: lines matching stripped from code (will be put
			inside ircd)
	* ircd/s_serv.c, s_serv_ext.h: m_kline() - completely re-written and
			moved from rusnet/; new commands wrappers for
			m_rline(), m_eline(), m_ukline(), m_urline(), 
			m_uneline()
	* ircd/s_serv.c, err.c: m_stats() added new RPL_STATSKLINE,
			RPL_STATSRLINE format
	* ircd/s_conf.c: initconf() make aconf->hold filled with expiration
			information for tlines.
	
2005-05-10 skold <chourf@deware.com>
	* ircd/ircd.c, support/config.h.dist: TIMEDKLINES removed from code
	* ircd/s_conf.c: find_kill() redesigned to reflect new K:line format
	* common/match.c, ircd/s_conf.c: match(), match_ipmask(): skip the 
		leading '=' matching in hostnames

